cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with the task of speech recognition and query-by-example search using acoustic word embeddings. Other likely sub-categories include "cs.SD" (Sound and Music Computing), "cs.LG" (Machine Learning), "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks), and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper presents new discriminative embedding models based on recurrent neural networks and explores the effects of network structure and dimensionality on the learned embeddings.
